# XV6 Kernel Debugging and System Call Development

## Description

This section focuses on understanding the internal behavior of the XV6 operating system through kernel debugging and system call implementation.

## Implemented Features

### GDB Debugging

Using GDB, the execution path of system calls was inspected by:

- Setting breakpoints inside the `syscall` function.
- Exploring the kernel call stack using `backtrace`.
- Inspecting process structures and trapframe values.
- Analyzing CPU privilege state.

### Custom System Call

A new system call similar to Linux `top` was implemented.

The system call provides information about active processes including:

- Process ID (PID)
- Process name
- Memory usage

